You know how in most movie climaxes that's where they try their hardest, well here, that's where they try their least.

00:16:59.140 --> 00:17:02.480
In fact, there's even a game on the app that's simply entitled,

00:17:02.480 --> 00:17:05.020
"The Lazier the Writer, The Faster the Paycheck"

00:17:05.840 --> 00:17:09.280
This is where you add up how many times the writer clearly didn't give a shit

00:17:09.280 --> 00:17:12.540
and just wrote down anything he wanted to get his pay cheque a little faster.

00:17:12.540 --> 00:17:13.860
Let's take a look.

00:17:14.140 --> 00:17:17.500
The aliens gave several trophies earlier, one of them being Q*bert

00:17:17.500 --> 00:17:21.580
and only now, several days later, think to ask him anything about their alien race.

00:17:21.580 --> 00:17:27.020
Sandler: So what's the history of your species as you watch me win "Call of Duty"? Eh, Doody.

00:17:27.020 --> 00:17:30.120
Nostalgia Critic: The aliens attack full force with all the pixellated characters which is neat

00:17:30.120 --> 00:17:33.240
but they make it clear that when they touch something it turns into pixels

00:17:33.240 --> 00:17:35.780
but when a crane stops Frogger, nothing happens.

00:17:35.780 --> 00:17:39.340
But really, who gives a shit when the president comes out and says this,

00:17:39.340 --> 00:17:42.360
Obama: They wanted to put me in a bunker. I said no thanks.

00:17:42.360 --> 00:17:46.000
Instead I'm going to fight video game aliens and err, save the world.

00:17:46.000 --> 00:17:46.500
[Pause sound effect]

00:17:46.500 --> 00:17:50.440
Nostalgia Critic: Actually, that would be pretty cool if Obama really did that.

00:17:51.120 --> 00:17:53.360
But he didn't, it was Kevin James. Put him back in there.

00:17:53.360 --> 00:17:58.440
Kevin James: Yay, your president, Paul Blart is going to shoot up aliens.

00:17:58.440 --> 00:18:00.660
Someone give me a beer to chug.

00:18:00.660 --> 00:18:01.160
[Pause sound effect]

00:18:01.160 --> 00:18:03.080
Nostalgia Critic: Now that's the stupidity I'm used to.

00:18:03.080 --> 00:18:05.900
It's like independence day only that was hilarious and this isn't.

00:18:05.900 --> 00:18:09.840
Unfunny pervert's video game character he fantasized over comes to life.

00:18:09.840 --> 00:18:13.020
Except she's not pixel-ly, she looks just like a real person.

00:18:13.620 --> 00:18:15.620
There is no reason for this.

00:18:15.620 --> 00:18:22.240
Oh yeah, and despite her not talking at all, she also falls in love with the unfunny pervert.

00:18:22.240 --> 00:18:24.460
There is again, no reason for this.

00:18:24.680 --> 00:18:28.220
Animated "writer": The less I try, the closer my money gets to me.

00:18:28.800 --> 00:18:34.860
Nostalgia Critic: So the aliens send a CG Max Headroom, that somehow looks even more fake than the original Max Headroom.

00:18:34.860 --> 00:18:40.920
to summon our heroes for one last challenge. Again, really no reason at all to give them a chance to win.

00:18:40.940 --> 00:18:45.420
But once again they have to play by the games rules so what do our heroes do?

00:18:45.420 --> 00:18:47.740
They cheat and don't play by the games rules.

00:18:47.740 --> 00:18:50.560
Yeah, remember that scene earlier saying how cheating was bad?

00:18:50.560 --> 00:18:53.600
Well that is exactly what they do, except it ends up winning the day.

00:18:53.600 --> 00:18:56.560
The only reason it's okay here is because it makes Adam Sandler look good.

00:18:56.560 --> 00:19:00.360
Animated "writer": Less talking, I'm almost rewarded for my incredible gift.

00:19:00.360 --> 00:19:07.480
Nostalgia Critic: This means all the pixels disappear including unfunny perv's love but it's okay because Q*bert turns into her.

00:19:08.100 --> 00:19:14.300
This is so blatantly lazy that even Sandler himself shrugs off how little this makes sense but doesn't give a shit.

00:19:14.500 --> 00:19:18.260
Sandler: Nobody questions why Q*bert suddenly turned into a hot lady?

00:19:19.100 --> 00:19:24.680
Oh well, who cares? We just wasted millions of dollars and doomed video game movies forever. Whoa!

00:19:24.680 --> 00:19:32.960
Animated "writer": I did it, I half-assed what thousands of writers have tried years to do for a living. Yay!

00:19:33.880 --> 00:19:42.440
Announcer Voice: And to preserve our comedic masterpiece, we're taking down every video on Vimeo that has the word "Pixels" in the title.

00:19:42.440 --> 00:19:47.660
Yes, we really did that. We're kind of f*cking insane.

00:19:47.660 --> 00:19:49.120
Oh, and while we're at it.

00:19:49.120 --> 00:19:54.680
We know what you want, we're so not behind the times.

00:19:57.800 --> 00:19:59.800
And that was "Pixels", one of the most hated films of the year.

00:19:59.800 --> 00:20:05.900
Is it one of the worst, if not, the worst Adam Sandler production that has ever been put together?

00:20:06.880 --> 00:20:07.520
No.

00:20:08.160 --> 00:20:10.160
It's not even close really.

00:20:10.160 --> 00:20:16.300
There are so many other films that he has had a hand in that tried less and accomplished less than this has.

00:20:16.840 --> 00:20:22.340
There was one or two neat effects and every twenty minutes maybe I had a little bit of a laugh

00:20:22.340 --> 00:20:24.860
which is more than I can say for some of his other productions.

00:20:25.060 --> 00:20:31.180
So, why is there so much hate? Why does this one get people just so f*cking pissed off?

00:20:32.940 --> 00:20:36.260
Because it's 20 f*cking 15.

00:20:37.180 --> 00:20:43.900
The fact that Sandler is still using these lazy gimmicks with no changes is just becoming insulting.

00:20:43.900 --> 00:20:49.600
Even if you don't like his humour which is totally understandable, you felt like he was at least trying.

00:20:49.600 --> 00:20:54.440
You felt like, even though it was weird there was some form of effort being put into his work before.

00:20:54.580 --> 00:20:58.040
Here it's like a $110 million dollar auto-pilot.

00:20:58.040 --> 00:21:02.780
We know Sandler, as well as all the people here can be both talented and funny.

00:21:02.780 --> 00:21:06.400
But as so many comedians are trying to evolve and adapt with the time

00:21:06.400 --> 00:21:10.280
Sandler seems bizarrely disinterested in getting better.

00:21:10.280 --> 00:21:15.940
I think we're angry because we want to like "Pixels". We want to like Sandler's work

00:21:15.940 --> 00:21:20.280
and when we find, it's not only bad but feels uncaring-ly bad,

00:21:20.280 --> 00:21:25.700
we wonder why no-one is waking up after all of these bombs and saying, lets try something different.

00:21:25.700 --> 00:21:29.300
Let's step up our game, step up our jokes, step up our characters.

00:21:29.300 --> 00:21:33.400
This is the tipping point where people are just saying, "Enough is Enough."

00:21:33.400 --> 00:21:38.040
"Give us effort again, give us energy, give us something that feels fresh and new."

00:21:38.040 --> 00:21:41.120
"Similar to the first surreal time that we've ever encountered you."

00:21:42.260 --> 00:21:45.160
Until then, we still have the Sandler App

00:21:45.160 --> 00:21:49.980
and hopefully there will be a day where this will no longer be a requirement in any of his films.

00:21:50.400 --> 00:21:52.940
I'm the Nostalgia Critic and...

00:21:53.660 --> 00:21:55.580
Come back.

